#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:5
msgid "Distributing F2PY extensions with ``meson-python``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:7
msgid ""
"The :ref:`f2py-meson` page covers building F2PY extensions using raw "
"``meson`` commands. This page shows how to package those extensions into "
"installable Python distributions (sdists and wheels) using `meson-python "
"<https://meson-python.readthedocs.io/>`_ as the PEP 517 build backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:12
msgid ""
"This is the recommended approach for distributing F2PY-wrapped Fortran code "
"as a Python package on PyPI or for local ``pip install`` workflows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:17
msgid ""
"``meson-python`` replaced ``setuptools`` / ``numpy.distutils`` as the "
"standard way to build and distribute compiled extensions in the NumPy and "
"SciPy ecosystem. See :ref:`distutils-status-migration` for background."
msgstr ""

