#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:146
msgid "Customizing the Fortran compiler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:148
msgid ""
"``meson-python`` delegates compiler selection to ``meson``. By default, "
"``meson`` will choose the first Fortran compiler it finds on the PATH. If "
"you want more control over Fortran compiler selection, set the ``FC`` "
"environment variable before building:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:153
msgid "FC=ifx python -m build --wheel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:157
msgid ""
"For more control, use a `Meson native file <https://mesonbuild.com/Native-"
"environments.html>`_:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:160
msgid ""
"; native.ini\n"
"[binaries]\n"
"fortran = 'ifx'\n"
"c = 'icx'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../f2py/buildtools/meson-python.rst:167
msgid "python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=\"--native-file=native.ini\""
msgstr ""

